form.form-content-approval action="{{site.baseurl}}/results/" method="get" 
  section
    p.introduction
      == "Working on a piece of content (or have an idea for one) and curious who needs to approve it for publication? Answer the following questions to help us point you in the right direction. If you still have questions, ask us in #{link_to "g-content", "https://18f.slack.com/messages/g-content"}"
  section.types
    h1 What type of content are you creating?
    p We rely on quite a few channels to get our message across. Scan the list below and check all that might apply to your content.
    span.instructions
      | I&rsquo;m creating&hellip;
      span.check-all-that-apply (check all that apply)
    fieldset.fieldset-content-types.fieldset-checkbox
      legend Content types
      .field.field-checkbox
        label for="content-type-internal-message" 
          input#content-type-internal-message name="content-type" type="checkbox" value="internal-message" /
          span.label-text
            span.label-text-title An internal message
            span.label-text-longdesc Any message for widely distributed internal consumption, such as Slack messages (#news), internal emails, and all-hands announcements. Not published to the public.
      .field.field-checkbox
        label for="content-type-internal-documentation" 
          input#content-type-internal-documentation name="content-type" type="checkbox" value="internal-documentation" /
          span.label-text
            span.label-text-title Internal documentation about how we work
            span.label-text-longdesc An article for internal consumption, shared with all new hires and used as reference by staff (also shared publicly whenever possible). Published at handbook.18f.gov.
      .field.field-checkbox
        label for="content-type-guide" 
          input#content-type-guide name="content-type" type="checkbox" value="guide" /
          span.label-text
            span.label-text-title A guide
            span.label-text-longdesc A long-form (> 1,000 words), public collection of information in a simple, standard style. Published at pages.18f.gov/ {guide-name}  and linked from guides.18f.gov.
      .field.field-checkbox
        label for="content-type-blog-post" 
          input#content-type-blog-post name="content-type" type="checkbox" value="blog-post" /
          span.label-text
            span.label-text-title A blog post
            span.label-text-longdesc A public article about how we work and what we&rsquo;re up to. Published at 18f.gsa.gov/blog.
      .field.field-checkbox
        label for="content-type-web-misc" 
          input#content-type-web-misc name="content-type" type="checkbox" value="web-misc" /
          span.label-text
            span.label-text-title I&rsquo;m not sure, but it&rsquo;ll be online!
            span.label-text-longdesc 18F occasionally publishes microsites outside of our standard guide format (pages.18f.gov/ {page-name} ). We&rsquo;ll work with you to publish content on any relevant subdomain.
  section.topics
    h1
      =="What is your content "
      em about?
    p Your content may require additional forms of approval if it substantially mentions a particular person or topic. What do we mean by substantially? If, for instance, you say &ldquo;Our project uses the U.S. Web Design Standards, which were originally built by 18F and USDS&hellip;&rdquo; you won&rsquo;t have to get clearance from USDS before publishing your content.
    span.instructions
      == "My content "
      em substantially
      == " mentions&hellip;"
      span.check-all-that-apply (check all that apply)
    fieldset.fieldset-checkbox.fieldset-content-topics
      legend Topics
      - @topics.each do |topic|
        .field.field-checkbox    
          label
            input name="content-topic" type="checkbox" value="#{topic.name}"
            span.label-text= topic.name
  section
    h1 Keeping up appearances
    p
      | While this finder works internally, our content is directly connected to stakeholders both internal
      em and
      | external. Help us out by preempting some potentially awkward conversations!
    span.instructions
      | My content might&hellip;
      span.check-all-that-apply (check all that apply)
    fieldset.fieldset-external-stakeholders.fieldset-checkbox
      legend External stakeholders
      .field.field-checkbox
        label for="content-external-stakeholders-press" 
          input#content-external-stakeholders-press name="content-external-stakeholders" type="checkbox" value="press" /
          span.label-text Generate interest from the press
      .field.field-checkbox
        label for="content-external-stakeholders-federal-partners" 
          input#content-external-stakeholders-federal-partners name="content-external-stakeholders" type="checkbox" value="federal-partners" /
          span.label-text Be perceived as critical of federal agencies or federal contractors.
  footer
    button type="submit"  Submit
